chamber /ˈtʃeɪmbə/

(chambers) 

1. N-COUNT A chamber is a large room, especially one that is used for formal meetings. 会议厅 

例： We are going to be in the council chamber every time he speaks. 我们每次都在会议厅听他讲话。 

2. N-COUNT You can refer to a country's legislature or to one section of it as a chamber . 议院 

例： More than 80 parties are contesting seats in the two-chamber parliament. 80多个政党在竞争该议会两院的席位。 

3. N-COUNT A chamber is a room designed and equipped for a particular purpose. (作特殊用途的) 房间 

例： For many, the dentist's office remains a torture chamber. 对许多人来说，牙科诊室仍是一间行刑室。

</div>

